"{\n \"cells\": [\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"source\": [\n    \"# ðŸŒ Concept 4: Local vs Global Scope\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"---\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"## Variable Scope\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"- ðŸ  **Local Scope**: Variables inside functions\\n\",\n    \"- ðŸŒ **Global Scope**: Variables outside functions\\n\",\n    \"- ðŸ”’ **Encapsulation**: Local variables are isolated\\n\",\n    \"- âš ï¸ **Best Practice**: Avoid global variables when possible\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"source\": [\n    \"![Visual representation of local and global variable scope with nested boxes showing function boundaries](images/scope_concept.png)\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"*Image illustrating how global variables sit outside functions, while local variables are confined within function boundaries.*\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"source\": [\n    \"### ðŸŒ Scope Example\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n   \"execution_count\": null,\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"outputs\": [],\n   \"source\": [\n    \"# Global variables\\n\",\n    \"ai_model = \\\"GPT-4\\\"\\n\",\n    \"total_requests = 0\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"def process_prompt(user_prompt):\\n\",\n    \"    # Local variables\\n\",\n    \"    processed_prompt = user_prompt.strip().lower()\\n\",\n    \"    response_length = len(processed_prompt) * 2\\n\",\n    \"    \\n\",\n    \"    # Access global variable (reading)\\n\",\n    \"    print(f\\\"Using model: {ai_model}\\\")\\n\",\n    \"    \\n\",\n    \"    # Modify global variable (needs global keyword)\\n\",\n    \"    global total_requests\\n\",\n    \"    total_requests += 1\\n\",\n    \"    \\n\",\n    \"    return f\\\"Processed: {processed_prompt[:50]}...\\\"\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"# Function call\\n\",\n    \"result = process_prompt('  Generate Python Code for Data Analysis  ')\\n\",\n    \"print(result)\\n\",\n    \"print(f\\\"Total requests: {total_requests}\\\")\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"# This would cause an error - local variable not accessible\\n\",\n    \"# print(processed_prompt)  # NameError!\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"source\": [\n    \"### ðŸ“¤ Output\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n   \"execution_count\": null,\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"outputs\": [],\n   \"source\": [\n    \"# Expected output:\\n\",\n    \"# Using model: GPT-4\\n\",\n    \"# Processed: generate python code for data analysis...\\n\",\n    \"# Total requests: 1\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"source\": [\n    \">*Scope helps keep your code organized and prevents variable conflicts!*\"\n   ]\n  },\n  {\n   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n   \"metadata\": {},\n   \"source\": [\n    \"### ðŸŽ¯ Key Takeaway\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"- Understanding scope prevents bugs and makes code more maintainable.\\n\",\n    \"- Local variables keep functions self-contained.\\n\",\n    \"- Global variables should be used sparingly.\\n\",\n    \"\\n\",\n    \"**ðŸ’­ Question:** Why might using too many global variables make your GenAI application harder to debug?\"\n   ]\n  }\n ],\n \"metadata\": {\n  \"kernelspec\": {\n   \"name\": \"python3\",\n   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n   \"language\": \"python\"\n  },\n  \"language_info\": {\n   \"name\": \"python\",\n   \"version\": \"3.x\"\n  }\n },\n \"nbformat\": 4,\n \"nbformat_minor\": 5\n}"